Market Development Manager job
in Singapore
Job Ref:
16691BR
COUNTRY:
Singapore
CITY:
Singapore
EMPLOYER:
INDUSTRY:
Marketing
Position Objective ThermoFisher Scientific is seeking an energetic, engaged and creative professional with expertise in developing and executing demand generation and channel management strategies in IPAC. In this role, you will be responsible for setting the ThermoFisher Scientific marketing strategies to grow life science instrument service and training revenues, the professional services portfolio and contract attachment sales. You will interact with a crossfunctional team within the IPAC region as well as a global marketing team to ensure voice of customer is included into global level strategy and that local implementation is optimized for the market.
Essential Functions
Designs marketing campaigns for generation of service and support revenues in IPAC
Implements new product launch strategies, including pricing and regional promotion
Ability to translate customer needs into effective messaging to drive demand for key offerings and communicating back to global product manager recommendations for the IPAC market
Understands competitive landscape and SWOT, using these principles to drive analysis and decision making
Creates project plans and dashboards to track and communicate marketing program effectiveness
Works in a highly collaborative environment with multiple stakeholders across the globe.
Trains, influences and interfaces with multiple sales teams to drive upfront sales
Uses multi-channel communication strategies to generate demand and hit revenue targets
Performs financial analysis and scenario planning
Additional and incidental duties related to the primary duties may be required for company business needs from time to time. Minimum Qualifications (must have)
Bachelor's degree (or equivalent knowledge and skills) in a Biology, Molecular biology, Chemistry or related discipline.
Minimum 5 Years Experience in Marketing of Life Sciences company
Excellent project management skills.
Excellent communication (verbal and written), negotiation, presentation, and interpersonal skills. Preferred Qualifications (nice to have)
Experience with Service Selling or Marketing is preferred EOE
Post Date:
04/28/2014
